<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6ef4200-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s56501"><num value="56501">§ 56501.</num><heading> Definition</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter, the term “essential vessel” means a vessel that is—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6ef4201-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s56501/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6ef4202-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s56501/1/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> security for a mortgage indebtedness to the United States Government; or</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6ef4203-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s56501/1/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> constructed under this subtitle or required by a contract under this subtitle to be operated on a certain essential foreign trade route; and</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6ef4204-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s56501/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> necessary in the interests of commerce and national defense to be maintained in condition for prompt use.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf6ef4205-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s8/c">Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(c)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1656">120 Stat. 1656</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
